docblock.description: Returns a Cache Item representing the specified key.
docblock.long-description: This method must always return a CacheItemInterface object, even in case of a cache miss. It MUST NOT return null.

tag.name: param
tag.description: The key for which to return the corresponding Cache Item.

tag.name: throws
tag.description: If the $key string is not a legal value a \Psr\Cache\InvalidArgumentException MUST be thrown.

tag.name: return
tag.description: The corresponding Cache Item.

docblock.description: Returns a traversable set of cache items.

tag.name: param
tag.description: An indexed array of keys of items to retrieve.

tag.name: throws
tag.description: If any of the keys in $keys are not a legal value a \Psr\Cache\InvalidArgumentException MUST be thrown.

tag.name: return
tag.description: A traversable collection of Cache Items keyed by the cache keys of each item. A Cache item will be returned for each key, even if that key is not found. However, if no keys are specified then an empty traversable MUST be returned instead.

docblock.description: Confirms if the cache contains specified cache item.
docblock.long-description: Note: This method MAY avoid retrieving the cached value for performance reasons. This could result in a race condition with CacheItemInterface::get(). To avoid such situation use CacheItemInterface::isHit() instead.

tag.name: param
tag.description: The key for which to check existence.

tag.name: throws
tag.description: If the $key string is not a legal value a \Psr\Cache\InvalidArgumentException MUST be thrown.

tag.name: return
tag.description: True if item exists in the cache, false otherwise.

docblock.description: Returns the key for the current cache item.
docblock.long-description: The key is loaded by the Implementing Library, but should be available to the higher level callers when needed.

tag.name: return
tag.description: The key string for this cache item.

docblock.description: Retrieves the value of the item from the cache associated with this object's key.
docblock.long-description:
The value returned must be identical to the value originally stored by set().
If isHit() returns false, this method MUST return null. Note that null is a legitimate cached value, so the isHit() method SHOULD be used to differentiate between "null value was found" and "no value was found."

tag.name: return
tag.description: The value corresponding to this cache item's key, or null if not found.

docblock.description: Confirms if the cache item lookup resulted in a cache hit.
docblock.long-description: Note: This method MUST NOT have a race condition between calling isHit() and calling get().

tag.name: return
tag.description: True if the request resulted in a cache hit. False otherwise.

docblock.description: Sets the value represented by this cache item.
docblock.long-description: The $value argument may be any item that can be serialized by PHP, although the method of serialization is left up to the Implementing Library.

tag.name: param
tag.description: The serializable value to be stored.

tag.name: return
tag.description: The invoked object.

docblock.description: Sets the expiration time for this cache item.

tag.name: param
tag.description: The point in time after which the item MUST be considered expired. If null is passed explicitly, a default value MAY be used. If none is set, the value should be stored permanently or for as long as the implementation allows.

tag.name: return
tag.description: The called object.

docblock.description: Sets the expiration time for this cache item.

tag.name: param
tag.description: The period of time from the present after which the item MUST be considered expired. An integer parameter is understood to be the time in seconds until expiration. If null is passed explicitly, a default value MAY be used. If none is set, the value should be stored permanently or for as long as the implementation allows.

tag.name: return
tag.description: The called object.

docblock.description: Returns the set expiration time as integer.
